The paper deals with the problem of detecting malicious PowerShell code, which is a cybersecurity issue, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) category. The paper also employs deep learning techniques, specifically contextual embeddings, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) categories. Additionally, the paper deals with the problem of labeled data scarcity, which is a common issue in software engineering, indicating that it could also belong to the cs.SE (Software Engineering) category. Finally, the paper uses real-world data and evaluates its models' performance, which suggests that it could also belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) category.
